received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/thc202/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false}],"milestone":null,"comments":17,"created_at":"2017-05-05T16:22:20Z","updated_at":"2020-02-02T08:38:54Z","closed_at":"2017-09-05T06:40:48Z","author_association":"NONE","type":null,"active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"Would it be possible to do something with font rendering in owasp zap on linux?\r\n\r\nPlease compare the request/response font rendering of owasp zap with burp:\r\n\r\n![screenshot from 2017-05-05 18-02-25](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/4216259/25753951/c387df2a-31bd-11e7-8b7a-89a853929f2f.png)\r\n\r\n![screenshot from 2017-05-05 18-00-44](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/4216259/25753961/cadab7de-31bd-11e7-990d-38c1ff2df5f4.png)\r\n\r\nThe screenshots were made on Kali xfce (but on pure Debian with gnome it looks similarly bad).\r\n\r\nI'm using `_JAVA_OPTIONS='-Dawt.useSystemAAFontSettings=gasp'` in `/etc/environment`. \r\n\r\n```\r\njava version \"1.8.0_131\"\r\nJava(TM) SE Runtime Environment (build 1.8.0_131-b11)\r\nJava HotSpot(TM) 64-Bit Server VM (build 25.131-b11, mixed mode)\r\n```\r\n\r\nI've also changed the interface font in zap (to Input Mono 16) - it looks slightly better with it.\r\n\r\nIt's hard to read the source/request/response code in zap, with better font rendering burp is much more pleasant in this regard. Shame, as zap is a great tool.\r\n\r\nThanks for your work.","closed_by":{"login":"psiinon","id":1081115,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEwODExMTU=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1081115?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/psiinon","html_url":"https://github.com/psiinon","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/psiinon/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/use